text.section:
Unless denied a license in accordance with KRS 304.9-440, a nonresident individual or business entity shall receive the applicable insurance producer license if:
The applicant is currently licensed as a resident and in good standing in his or her home state;
The applicant has submitted the proper request for license and has paid the fees required by KRS 304.4-010 and administrative regulations;
The applicant has submitted or transmitted to the commissioner the application for a license that the applicant submitted to his or her home state or a completed uniform individual application or uniform business entity application; and
The applicant's home state awards nonresident licenses to residents of this state on the same basis.
